# Servio Code Quality Rules

## Type Safety
- NO `as any` types allowed
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces
- Use Zod for runtime validation
- Prefer `unknown` over `any` for unknowns

## Testing
- All API routes must have tests
- Test happy path + error cases
- Mock external dependencies

## Code Quality
- No console.log (removed in production)
- Use logger for errors (Sentry integration)
- ESLint warnings must be addressed
- TypeScript strict mode enforced

